public enum TransactionType
extends java.lang.Enum<TransactionType>

Specifies the transaction type to use when enqueuing messages into a transactional queue.

Enum Constant Detail

None

public static final TransactionType None

Specifies that the call is not part of a transaction. This transaction type cannot be used to send a message to a transactional queue.

Equivalent to MSMQ's MQ_NO_TRANSACTION.

MTS

public static final TransactionType MTS

If the application is running in the context of a COM+ (Component Services) transaction, the message is sent within the current COM+ transaction. Otherwise, the message is sent outside of a transaction.

Equivalent to MSMQ's MQ_MTS_TRANSACTION.

XA

public static final TransactionType XA
Specifies that the call is part of an externally coordinated, XA-compliant transaction.

SINGLE_MESSAGE

public static final TransactionType SINGLE_MESSAGE
Specifies that the message is sent in a single-message transaction. Messages sent in a single-message transaction must be sent to a transactional queue.

Equivalent to MSMQ's MQ_SINGLE_MESSAGE.
